Hi, we're Lauren, Michelle, & Tricia

We will be talking about aircraft collisions with various types of wildlife (2000-) using data from the Federal Aviation Administration. Site: https://opendata.socrata.com/Government/FAA-National-Wildlife-Aircraft-Strike-Database-Yea/9r8b-gr46/data

## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

American kestrels and red-tailed hawks are two common birds of prey. Let's compare the average speeds of the aircrafts when they collided with these birds.

## Warning: Removed 1783 rows containing non-finite values (stat_boxplot).

Based on the boxplot, do you think these speeds are above average, average, or below average compared to other species?

These speeds lie near the peak of the distribution, suggesting that they are average.

Let's see what the real average speed is and compare these speeds to the average.
